headline: TPR Q4 Deep Dive: Global Expansion, Gen Z Growth Drive Results and Guidance
summary: Luxury fashion conglomerate Tapestry (NYSE:TPR) reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales up 14% year on year to $2.50 billion. The company’s full-year revenue guidance of $7.75 billion at the midpoint came in 4.8% above analysts’ estimates. Its GAAP profit of $2.68 per share was 20.5% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
